Package uk.co.flax.biosolr.ontology.core

Class OntologyDataBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.flax.biosolr.ontology.core.OntologyDataBuilder

  • public class OntologyDataBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    Builder class for OntologyData objects.

    This class should be used with an OntologyHelper to retrieve and build the ontology data for a specific class. For example: 

            OntologyData data = new OntologyBuilder(helper, iri)
                .includeSynonyms(true)
                .includeRelations(false)
                .build();
    Author:
    Matt Pearce

      • includeIndirect

        public OntologyDataBuilder includeIndirect​(boolean inc)
        Set whether or not the builder should include indirect (more than one step removed) parent/child relationships. If set true, the OntologyData item will include descendants and ancestors.
        Parameters:
        inc - set true to include indirect hierarchical relationships.
        Returns:
        the OntologyDataBuilder.

      • includeRelations

        public OntologyDataBuilder includeRelations​(boolean inc)
        Set whether or not the builder should include additional relationships (ie. "is part of", "has disease location", etc.). If set true, the OntologyData item will include relationIris and relationLabels.
        Parameters:
        inc - set true to include additional relationships.
        Returns:
        the OntologyDataBuilder.
